    {
      "id": "08654b2a-e50c-4d51-bf12-d2dc36aef9f8",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Déterminer les lois marginales du couple $(X,Y)$ puis calculer $\\mathbb{E}(X)$ et $\\mathbb{E}(Y)$.",
        "html": "<p>Déterminer les lois marginales du couple <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\((X,Y)\\)</span> puis calculer <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\mathbb{E}(X)\\)</span> et <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\mathbb{E}(Y)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "276f0560-7d52-4145-a7e0-a6a7e02d1ba5",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "\\begin{itemize}\n\t\t\t\\item $\\prob(X = 1) = \\frac{1}{3}$, $\\prob(X = 2) = \\frac{1}{3}$, $\\prob(X = 3) = \\frac{1}{3}$.\n\t\t\t\\item $\\prob(Y = 1) = \\frac{1}{6}$, $\\prob(Y = 2) = \\frac{1}{3}$, $\\prob(Y = 3) = \\frac{1}{3}$, $\\prob(Y = 4) = \\frac{1}{6}$.\n\t\t\t\\item $\\mathbb{E}(X) = \\sum\\limits_{i=1}^{3} i \\times \\prob(X = i) = 1 \\times \\frac{1}{3} + 2 \\times \\frac{1}{3} + 3 \\times \\frac{1}{3} = 2$.\n\t\t\t\\item $\\mathbb{E}(Y) = \\sum\\limits_{i=1}^{4} i \\times \\prob(Y = i) = 1 \\times \\frac{1}{6} + 2 \\times \\frac{1}{3} + 3 \\times \\frac{1}{3} + 4 \\times \\frac{1}{6} = 2.5$.\n\t\t\\end{itemize}",
        "html": "<ul>\n<li><p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\prob(X = 1) = \\frac{1}{3}\\)</span>,\n<span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\prob(X = 2) = \\frac{1}{3}\\)</span>, <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\prob(X = 3) = \\frac{1}{3}\\)</span>.</p></li>\n<li><p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\prob(Y = 1) = \\frac{1}{6}\\)</span>,\n<span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\prob(Y = 2) = \\frac{1}{3}\\)</span>, <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\prob(Y = 3) = \\frac{1}{3}\\)</span>, <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\prob(Y = 4) = \\frac{1}{6}\\)</span>.</p></li>\n<li><p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\mathbb{E}(X) = \\sum\\limits_{i=1}^{3}\ni \\times \\prob(X = i) = 1 \\times \\frac{1}{3} + 2 \\times \\frac{1}{3} + 3\n\\times \\frac{1}{3} = 2\\)</span>.</p></li>\n<li><p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\mathbb{E}(Y) = \\sum\\limits_{i=1}^{4}\ni \\times \\prob(Y = i) = 1 \\times \\frac{1}{6} + 2 \\times \\frac{1}{3} + 3\n\\times \\frac{1}{3} + 4 \\times \\frac{1}{6} = 2.5\\)</span>.</p></li>\n</ul>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "51aaad12-b1dc-4d1a-b36b-b0dc8ef2f0cc",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Les variables aléatoires $X$ et $Y$ sont-elles indépendantes ?",
        "html": "<p>Les variables aléatoires <span class=\"math inline\">\\(X\\)</span> et\n<span class=\"math inline\">\\(Y\\)</span> sont-elles indépendantes ?</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "aaa48940-6e3e-438d-98a9-25d9c14faace",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Non, car $\\prob(X = 1, Y = 1) = \\frac{1}{6} \\neq \\prob(X = 1) \\times \\prob(Y = 1) = \\frac{1}{3} \\times \\frac{1}{6} = \\frac{1}{18}$.",
        "html": "<p>Non, car <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\prob(X = 1, Y = 1) =\n\\frac{1}{6} \\neq \\prob(X = 1) \\times \\prob(Y = 1) = \\frac{1}{3} \\times\n\\frac{1}{6} = \\frac{1}{18}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "145ae4f3-6ef4-4648-9582-d085784f8a14",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "On pose $Z = X - Y$. Déterminer la loi du couple $(X,Z)$. Les variables aléatoires $X$ et $Z$ sont-elles indépendantes ?",
        "html": "<p>On pose <span class=\"math inline\">\\(Z = X - Y\\)</span>. Déterminer la\nloi du couple <span class=\"math inline\">\\((X,Z)\\)</span>. Les variables\naléatoires <span class=\"math inline\">\\(X\\)</span> et <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(Z\\)</span> sont-elles indépendantes ?</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "247ee3fd-db65-479c-8e34-fb8ad14f305e",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "L'ensemble des valeurs prises par $Z$ est $\\{-3, -2, -1, 0, 1, 2\\}$. On a $\\prob(X = 1, Z = -2) = \\prob(X = 1, Y = 3) = 0$. De même, on obtient le tableau de la loi du couple $(X,Z)$ : \n\n\\begin{center}\n\t\\begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|c|c|c|c|c|}\n\t\t\\hline\n\t\t$X/Z$ & -3 & -2 & -1 & 0 & 1 & 2 & $\\prob(X = x)$ \\\\\n\t\t\\hline\n\t\t1 & 0 & 0 & $\\frac{1}{6}$ & $\\frac{1}{6}$ & $0$ & $0$ & $\\frac{1}{3}$ \\\\\n\t\t\\hline\n\t\t2 & 0 & 0 & $\\frac{1}{6}$ & $\\frac{1}{6}$ & $0$ & $0$ & $\\frac{1}{3}$ \\\\\n\t\t\\hline\n\t\t13 & 0 & 0 & $\\frac{1}{6}$ & $\\frac{1}{6}$ & $0$ & $0$ & $\\frac{1}{3}$ \\\\\n\t\t\\hline\n\t\t$\\prob(Z = z)$ & $0$ & $0$ & $\\frac{1}{2}$ & $\\frac{1}{2}$ & $0$ & $0$ & 1 \\\\\n\t\t\\hline\n\t\\end{tabular}\n\\end{center}\nOn en déduit que les variables aléatoires $X$ et $Z$ sont indépendantes (toutes les colonnes sont proportionnelles entre elles).",
        "html": "<p>L’ensemble des valeurs prises par <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(Z\\)</span> est <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\{-3,\n-2, -1, 0, 1, 2\\}\\)</span>. On a <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\prob(X =\n1, Z = -2) = \\prob(X = 1, Y = 3) = 0\\)</span>. De même, on obtient le\ntableau de la loi du couple <span class=\"math inline\">\\((X,Z)\\)</span>\n:</p>\n<div class=\"center\">\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"header\">\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(X/Z\\)</span></th>\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\">-3</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\">-2</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\">-1</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\">0</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\">1</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\">2</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\prob(X =\nx)\\)</span></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">0</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">0</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\frac{1}{6}\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\frac{1}{6}\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(0\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(0\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\frac{1}{3}\\)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">0</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">0</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\frac{1}{6}\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\frac{1}{6}\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(0\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(0\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\frac{1}{3}\\)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">13</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">0</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">0</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\frac{1}{6}\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\frac{1}{6}\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(0\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(0\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\frac{1}{3}\\)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\prob(Z =\nz)\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(0\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(0\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\frac{1}{2}\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\frac{1}{2}\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(0\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(0\\)</span></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p>On en déduit que les variables aléatoires <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(X\\)</span> et <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(Z\\)</span> sont indépendantes (toutes les colonnes\nsont proportionnelles entre elles).</p>\n"
      }
